@KMW.  I am a never Trumper from way back, as are many of my friends.  I assure you that, despite the rhetoric, I do not know anyone who hates our president.  What I — and many other millions of Americans — object to is President Trump’s lack of competence, his inability to comprehend and consider facts, and his visible lack of empathy for the citizens of this country who will get sick and die unnecessarily due to his administration’s slow response.  Some may see this as “venom,” but the truth must be told: This type of pandemic was predicted and our president ignored the warnings, ignored the results of simulations that told us we were unprepared, and he ultimately put his needs above the country’s. 

No president could have fully prevented this siege, but a competent leader could have acted more decisively (as many have around the world). Like it or not, our president has demonstrated again and again that he is a man of poor character, and that is now costing American lives. 

That, sir, is news.

